labels.value: This workflow is initiated when an invoice cannot be posted because goods receipt has not been done (or receipt in a lower quantity than that on the invoice.

A price variance workflow is started when the price mentioned in an invoice is different from the price mentioned in a Purchase Order or Scheduling Agreement. When there is a price variance, the invoice is blocked for payment. After completing the workflow approval, the invoice could be automatically unblocked and released for payment in SAP.

A quantity variance workflow is started when the quantity of an item mentioned in an invoice is different from the quantity mentioned in a Goods Receipt posted or when the Goods Receipt is not posted. When there is a quantity variance, the invoice is blocked for payment. After the Goods Receipt is posted and workflow is approved, the invoice is automatically unblocked and released for payment.

A functional correctness workflow is used to process or approve service invoices. When this workflow is started, the invoice is blocked for payment. After the workflow is approved, the invoice could be unblocked and released for payment in SAP.

An unplanned delivery costs workflow is used for the approval of additional costs, such as, delivery costs and packing costs that are not planned in a Purchase Order by the responsible Purchase Department. When this workflow is initiated, the invoice is blocked for payment. After completing the workflow approval, the invoice could be unblocked and released for payment in SAP.
Applicable to workflows with non-PO related invoices. Payment will be released after the price and facts have been approved.
This WF is used to approve the prices of framework, limit & blanket purchase orders with PO type FO, YB where the Purchase Order unit is AB, AU, DL, LE, SRV, or ZZ.
